HEADWORD: Burton
<hw>Bur"ton</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OE. & Prov. E.
<ets>bort</ets> to press or indent anything.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A peculiar tackle, formed of two or more blocks, or pulleys, the
weight being suspended to a hook block in the bight of the running
part.</def>⟦br⟧
